CONTRIBUTING

This project welcomes contributions from anyone, including BAS/NERC employees, contractors and others under the following guidelines:

* These are general guidelines used by this project, they do not represent any formal policy or notice.

* The preferred method of integrating contributions is through a Git pull request.

* The preferred method of raising issues is through the NERC Jira issue tracker, or via e-mail if external to NERC.

* If contributing code, please follow any defined coding standards where specified, or any obvious conventions implied within the code.

* See the contributing section of the end-user documentation for additional information [1]

* Please see either the "NERC STAFF" or "EXTERNAL" section as appropriate to you.


NERC STAFF

For reporting issues please see this project within the NERC Jira issue tracker [2]


EXTERNAL

For reporting issues please e-mail the BAS Web & Applications Team [3]. You will be contacted by a member of this team directly.


[1] https://bas-style-kit.web.nerc-bas.ac.uk/

[2] https://jira.ceh.ac.uk/BSK

[3] basweb@bas.ac.uk


Last updated: July 2015
Contact address: basweb@bas.ac.uk (BAS Web & Applications Team)
